    "id": "Cascadia_highRes_Vp_Ashraf2025",
    "title": "3D high-resolution P-wave velocity model",
    "summary": "The study develops a high-resolution 3D P-wave velocity model of the south-central Cascadia subduction zone using wide-angle seismic refraction data from shipborne active-source seismic shots recorded on ocean-bottom seismometers and onshore seismic stations. A tomographic inversion approach incorporating travel-time data of multiple seismic phases (Pg, Pn, PmP) was used to resolve crustal and subducting slab structures, with iterative modeling to refine velocity distributions and slab topography.",
